桜エンド（ハッピーエンド）

▶Defeat the False Buddha in the inner chamber 4 of the
Alakapart to unlock the True End.

Would you like to see how to defeat the False Buddha? *It is
recommended to view it after clearing it once, as it contains
spoilers.

If you want to start over from the Horror Part, in addition to the
condition of clearing the Horror Part without being tempted by the
safe, the following two points are important.

①Do not investigate unnecessary things (If you investigate unnecessary
things, the protagonist will be protected by Araka and suffer from
aftereffects, weakening her) ② In the event of contact with the three
shadows, choose to accept (The shadows are Araka. When you come into
contact with them, Araka is strengthened by touching the pure energy)

The above conditions can be fulfilled by not investigating things
related to Araka and not investigating suspicious things, allowing you
to skip the Horror Part and proceed from normal play. Since the events
with scenes do not affect the Araka Part, you can also see all the H
scenes.

2. Unlocking Enlightenment from the recent save data In the
Alakapart, after being defeated by the third boss Mofuki, if you meet
the following conditions, Araka will awaken and be strengthened. ※
There is no need to start a new game with this method.

① 1. Consume a certain number of Perception Events 2. Endure
humiliation for a certain amount of time in the Defeat in Battle Log
Event 3. Choose Even if it means washing in muddy water a certain
number of times during battle  These conditions are calculated based
on the total number of occurrences and are determined upon respawning
after defeat in battle.

The third boss Mofuki cannot be fought unless you have been
defeated by the second boss Yainmeijin. However, if you load the most
recent save data and are defeated by the False Buddha, the battle will
resume from either before Yainmeijin or before Mofuki depending on the
defeat situation.

The above information can also be confirmed from the enclosed spoiler
flowchart.

▶True End ~ Epilogue. To unlock the After ~ condition,
defeat the False Buddha in Araka Path Back Palace 4.

Would you like to see how to defeat the False Buddha? *It is
recommended to view it after clearing it once, as it contains
spoilers.

1. If you want to start over from the Horror Path, in
addition to the condition of clearing the Horror Path without being
tempted by the safe, the following two points are important.

①Do not investigate unnecessary things (If Araka protects the
protagonist from being absorbed into the other world by investigating
unnecessary things, she will suffer from aftereffects and weaken) ② In
the event of contact with the three shadows, choose to accept (The
shadows are Araka. When you make contact, Araka is strengthened by
touching the pure energy)

The above conditions can be fulfilled by investigating things related
to Araka and not investigating suspicious things, both from the Horror
Path skip function and from normal play. Since events with scenes do
not affect the Araka path, you can also see all H scenes.

2. Unlocking Enlightenment from the recent save data In the Araka
Path, after being defeated by the third boss, Butsu Fuki, if you meet
the following conditions, Araka will awaken and become stronger. *You
do not need to start a new game with this method.

① 1. Consume a certain number of Perception Events 2. Endure
humiliation for a certain amount of time in the Defeat Log Event 3.
Choose Even if it means washing in muddy water a certain number of
times during battle  These conditions are calculated based on the
total number of occurrences and are determined upon respawning after
defeat in battle.

The third boss, Butsu Fuki, can only be fought if you have
not been defeated by the second boss, Yain Myojin. However, if you
load the most recent save data and are defeated by the False Buddha,
you will be respawned either in front of Yain Myojin or in front of
Butsu Fuki, depending on the defeat situation.

The above information can also be confirmed from the enclosed spoiler
flowchart.

▶True End ~ Epilogue. To unlock the previous content, defeat
the False Buddha in the depths of Araka Path 4.

Do you want to see how to defeat the False Buddha? *It is recommended
to view it after clearing it once, as it contains spoilers.

1. If you want to start over from the Horror Path, in
addition to the condition of clearing the Horror Path without being
tempted by the safe, the following two points are important.

①Do not investigate unnecessary things (If Araka protects the
protagonist from being absorbed into the other world by investigating
unnecessary things, she will suffer from aftereffects and weaken) ② In
the event of contact with the three shadows, choose to accept (The
shadows are Araka. When you make contact, Araka is strengthened by
touching the pure energy)

The above conditions can be fulfilled by investigating things related
to Araka and not investigating suspicious things, both from the Horror
Path skip function and from normal play. Since the events with scenes
do not affect the Araka Path, you can also see all the H scenes.

2. Unlocking Enlightenment from the recent save data In the
Araka Path, after being defeated by the third boss Monfuki, if you
meet the following conditions, Araka will awaken and become stronger.
※There is no need to start a new game with this method.

①1. Consume a certain number of Perception Events 2. Endure
humiliation for a certain amount of time in the Defeat Log Event after
battle 3. Choose Even if it means washing in muddy water a certain
number of times during battle. It will be calculated based on the
total number of times and determined upon respawning after defeat.

You cannot fight the third boss Monfuki unless you have
been defeated by the second boss Yainmeijin. However, if you load the
most recent save data and are defeated by the False Buddha, you will
be restarted from either before Yainmeijin or before Monfuki depending
on the defeat situation.

The above content can also be confirmed from the enclosed spoiler
flowchart.
